HEADWORD: Knowable
<hw>Know"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>That may be known;
capable of being discovered, understood, or ascertained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus mind and matter, as known or <qex>knowable</qex>, are only
two different series of phenomena or qualities.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton. </qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knowa bleness</ent>⟦br⟧
